adverbs.description: weedily (comparative more weedily, superlative most weedily)

entries.meaning: In a weedy state; full of weeds.
examples: The old-fashioned stoop, with its suggestive benches on either side, lay solitary and silent in the moonlight; the garden path, weedily overgrown since father's death, and sentineled here and there with ragged hollyhock, lay quiet and dew-laden  […]
